Canadian singer Justin Bieber has cancelled the remaining dates of his Justice World Tour following a health battle. The singer had earlier announced that he is suffering from Ramsay-Hunt Syndrome, which left his face partially paralyzed and would be taking a break from performing in September 2022. The singer, who turned 29 on Wednesday, cancelled the tour short due to his ongoing recovery from Ramsay Hunt syndrome. The news was announced on the tour’s official Twitter page on Tuesday saying, “Justin Bieber has officially CANCELLED the remaining dates of his ‘Justice World Tour’. Check in with your point of purchase for refunds for your show dates.”